&lt;p&gt;We could do an A/B test against govdocs1 and see what happens. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14310014" author="mikemccand" created="Fri, 6 Feb 2015 21:59:32 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;I have hesitation about changing the original logic, because I&apos;m not sure why if(inParagraph) was added...maybe for properly closing formatting?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t remember why...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;would be more general and handle the formatting stuff properly?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think that may be safer?  In case there was pending styling that needs to be closed ...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think if Tika&apos;s tests pass with that change you should commit!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
